For basic, hearty Italian comfort food, it's hard to find better than Olazzo. The Pietrobono brothers established their first Olazzo in Bethesda, then expanded that location, and later opened a second location in Silver Spring. Both have a full menu of standard Italian appetizers and entrees (including multiple pastas, veal, chicken, eggplant, shrimp, and daily specials - most starting with warm bread and olive oil/balsamic vinegar and a house salad), a diverse wine and martini list, and tasty desserts to have you feel happy and sated. Outdoor seating is available in good weather, and the booths and tables inside feel warm and cozy in colder months. The well-trained servers casual and friendly attention make each meal enjoyable. When you want solid, standard Italian comfort food served well, go to Olazzo.

After an hour of Pokemon Go raiding in Bethesda, we asked a friend for a great date night restaurant for Italian cuisine and she said we must go to Olazzo in Woodmont Triangle. When we arrived, there was short wait for a table as they had to clean off one for us.  The restaurant had dimmed lighting, which gave off a romantic and intimate setting. The walls were a warm yellow color and covered with framed photographs and black and white paintings. In the back of the room, there was a tv playing old films. In the background, they had light music playing.  Their food and drink menu is straightforward. They had a notable wine list. Being a weeknight, we opted out for wine. My boyfriend ordered a few beers while I slowly enjoy a glass of limoncello.  Before placing food order, our server Emma brought us  a basket of warm italian bread and a balsamic vinegar and olive oil dipping sauce. The bread was crispy around the edges and soft in the middle.  The service was excellent throughout our dining experience. Emma was warm, friendly, and hospitable. She checked up on us to see if we needed anything else.  For appetizers, we shared an order of Stuffed Dates, which consisted of four medjool dates stuffed with creamy and smooth goat cheese, wrapped in crispy pancetta, served in a sweet chanti reduction, and garnished with fresh herbs.  For dinner, my boyfriend ordered the Salmon Mango, which consisted of a grilled lightly seasoned salmon filet sauteed with a vegetable medley and served with a mango salsa. The vegetable medley consisted of bell peppers, mushrooms, red onions, and broccoli. If you like the taste of peppers, this is a dish you'll love. I ordered the Ravioli Rose, which consisted of six round raviolis filled with a cheese blend of ricotta, parmesan, romano, and mozzarella, served with tomato cream sauce, and garnished with fresh basil. The creamy tomato sauce was light but still enjoyable.  Each entree came with a house salad, which consisted of romaine, spring greens, cucumbers, and red onion tossed in homemade vinaigrette. It was delicious.  For desserts, we debated between the Blueberry Cheesecake and Tiramisu but went with the latter. The Tiramisu consisted of square shaped cake made of espresso and liqueur dipped savoiardi cookies, sweetened mascarpone, and cocoa powder. I liked how it was light and fluffy dessert.

Recap areas of immediate improvement: 1. Food safety 2. Hostess - poor communication and etiquette 3. Excellent food and atmosphere! The folks at Olazzo really go out of their way to make you feel at home and comfortable. The food is always great here, just wish there were more drink specials so when friends and i get a drink with our food, it doesn't run into the $30+ great decor since they did the changes over a year ago. We ended up asking the busser to bring us more bread. But the bread is always great! Hence the 2nd helping ;)  i always recommend other this place to my other friends and they say they love it as well.

Updating my review as we've been here a few times over the past year. We happened upon Olazzo one night, fully expecting to be disappointed. We even walked past it several times trying to avoid it, but its neighbors didn't look any better. Everything was delicious — wine selection is great, pastas are tasty, mains are well executed. We liked it so much we went back the next week with a party of ten, all of whom were delighted. Since then we've been back a few times and each time has been decent, but not terrific. Pastas are a bit overdone, service painfully slow. It's very popular, which may explain the hit or miss experience. Worth a shot but no longer fantastic.

I just recently tried Olazzo and absolutely loved it. We had a party of 4 on a Friday night and they did a great job of accommodating us with outside seating. I had the Seafood pasta special, which can taste horrible if not done right. However, Olazzo did a great job! The seafood was fresh and the pasta tasted delicious. I would definitely recommend this location to others.

I met my two best friends there for dinner and drinks.  The wait staff was exceptional.  They were attentive and didn't get exasperated when we weren't sure what to order the first three times they came around.  The food was amazing.  I had the Chicken Cardinale, which is a chicken penne pasta dish with a vodka cream sauce and sun-dried tomatoes. I loved the ambiance.  Very rustic, warm, and tuscanish (yes, I made up a word).  I would definitely go there again. Great for any type of engagement and group.
